ados is their first employer with formal pay benefits and training arcos dorados has a structured training program that helps with personal and professional development mcdonald’s university trains restaurant managers midmanagers and ownersoperators on best practices in restaurant and people management sales marketing and accounting additional management training curriculums are available for employees who want to advance within the company more than  people from across latin america have participated in mcdonald’s university courses and educational activities a  survey of  firms in latin america and the caribbean indicated that half of the companies across the region are struggling to find qualified employees in april  arcos dorados became one of the first companies to join the new employment opportunities neo program developed by the interamerican development bank and the international youth foundation the program helps to increase the employability of the region’s youth its goal is to increase job entry among poor and low income young people corporate participation in the program involves an initial investment from sponsors of  million in cash and inkind resourcescitation needed arcos dorados is consistently ranked as one of the best places to work in latin america the great place to work institute ranked the company fourth among the top  best multinational employers in latin america in  and sixth in  and it led the súper empresas super companies ranking by the expansióncnn magazine the company has strong relationships with unions in many countries and includes unionized labor among its workers in brazil some unions have challenged the company on parttime or flexible working hours charityedit one of arcos dorados’ major charitable causes is the ronald mcdonald house charities as of  there were  ronald mcdonald house charities programs in  countries in latin america and the caribbean this includes  ronald mcdonald houses  ronald mcdonald family rooms and one ronald mcdonald care mobile which was built to deliver pediatric care services to remote locations mchappy day mcdonald’s global fundraiser for rmhc raises money for various children’s causes including the ronald mcdonald house charities foundation through proceeds from the sales of big macs in  mchappy day in latin america raised nearly  million for rmhc environmental and social responsibilityedit sustainable food sourcingedit there are many myths and misperceptions about the quality of mcdonald’s products including ingredients and additives in its beef products a recent television and online campaign by arcos dorados called beyond our kitchen or mas alla de la cocina highlights the origin of the ingredients used in mcdonald’s restaurants and  addresses questions about the quality of mcdonald’s food by showing the farms where the beef chicken potatoes and vegetables come from and how the food is handled and processed before making its way to a mcdonalds restaurant globally mcdonald’s has worked with animal welfare expert dr temple grandin since the mids to help ensure animals in the supply chain are properly cared for mcdonalds is currently in discussion with its pork suppliers to explore ways to phase out gestation stalls for pigs and is working with producers and suppliers to develop traceability systems to prove that the meat it buys is not from farms that use gestation stalls mcdonald’s became a member of the global roundtable for sustainable beef grsb in  the group is working to advance the sustainable production of beef through the commitment of stakeholders in the beef value chain one hundred percent of arcos dorados’ beef and oil suppliers have committed to ending procurement of any goods produced as a consequence of any forest clearance from the amazon supply chainedit all of arcos dorados food and paper suppliers comply with mcdonald’s supplier workplace accountability policy which stipulates that workers are compensated and treated fairly work in safe conditions and produce high quality foods and packaging arcos dorados also surveys and audits its suppliers in latin america and the caribbean to ensure their operations meet mcdonald’s quality health and safety standards the company has check points throughout the supply chain to ensure food safety cleanliness and consistency based on globally recognized established industry standards including the international organization for standardization iso the british retail consortium brc and the hazard analysis critical control plan haccp reducing consumptionedit mcdonald’s restaurants use a significant amount of energy specifically in cold storage to protect food safety during the past several years arcos dorados implemented a restaurant maintenance strategy to reduce water consumption energy utilization where possible and waste reduction at its restaurants as one example the company developed a collection and storage system for the water generated through condensation from the air conditioning equipment they used the collected water to clean external areas and to water plants reducing daily water consumption at one restaurant in brazil from  liters to  liters referencesedit  a b arcos dorados holdings reports fourthquarter and fullyear fiscal  results with record annual revenues eps operating margin and new bookings pdf arcos dorados holdings inc retrieved november   check date values in accessdate help  number of company employees   a b company description in homepage   a b c the companys description in reuters   arcos dorados plays pivotal role in  fifa world cup™ preparations yahoo finance  retrieved    a b c d e arcos dorados holdings inc  f  for  sec info retrieved    chairman and ceo of arcos dorados woods staton  latin trade group latintradecom  retrieved    patton leslie  mcdonald’s operator arcos dorados soars after initial offer bloomberg retrieved    latin america news latinvex retrieved    is arcos dorados a better pick than mcdonalds betafoolcom retrieved    a b 